    "narrative": "Our primary offensive engine today features **Mickey Moniak** (75.98) and **Corbin Carroll** (71.33), who represent the highest upside in our lineup. **Mickey Moniak** benefits immensely from a favorable encounter with Sasaki, where a 14% park boost and a significant dynamic platoon advantage vault him into elite territory. Meanwhile, **Corbin Carroll** remains a must-start despite facing a tough arm in Gausman; his elite xwOBA and the premium order placement in the #2 spot provide a high floor for Runs and SB potential. **Max Muncy** (71.26) also provides elite output today, capitalizing on a weak Schultz matchup where a 19% boost in SP skill projection aligns with his power profile against left-handed pitching.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench was prioritizing **Jose Caballero** (52.65) over **Alex Freeland** (52.07). While **Jose Caballero** faces a steep challenge against the dominant Ragans (2.52 xERA), his dynamic platoon advantage remains high, and his utility in our scarcity-driven SB hunt outweighs the marginally higher projection for **Alex Freeland**, whose #9 lineup slot creates a significant drag on his overall efficiency. Conversely, **Vinnie Pasquantino** (51.32) was omitted due to a heavy negative platoon adjustment against Weathers, effectively capping his ceiling for the day.\n\nWe are keeping a close eye on the catchers and high-velocity arms today; specifically, the presence of elite catchers behind the plate provides a minor drag on the output of **Seiya Suzuki**, **James Wood**, and **Austin Riley**. While **James Wood** still earns a strong 66.69 rating due to his #1 spot in the order, the situational risks of facing Ray mean we need him to remain aggressive on the basepaths to justify the lineup spot. We are also monitoring the status of **Giancarlo Stanton**, who remains unavailable; until he returns to the active lineup, we will continue to rely on the depth provided by **Tyler Soderstrom** and **Trevor Story** to maintain our competitive edge in the 5x5 categories.",
